children.comment: Return a PEP 440-compliant version number from VERSION.

children.name: update
children.comment: Extend rather than replace existing key lists.

children.name: lists
children.comment: Yield (key, list) pairs.

children.name: capfirst
children.comment: Capitalize the first letter of a string.

children.name: get_bytes_from_wsgi
children.comment:
Get a value from the WSGI environ dictionary as bytes.

key and default should be strings.

children.name: _get_response
children.comment:
Resolve and call the view, then apply view, exception, and
template_response middleware. This method is everything that happens
inside the request/response middleware.

children.name: copy
children.comment: Return a mutable copy of this object.

children.name: _load_post_and_files
children.comment: Populate self._post and self._files if the content-type is a form type

children.name: build_absolute_uri
children.comment:
Build an absolute URI from the location and the variables available in
this request. If no ``location`` is specified, build the absolute URI
using request.get_full_path(). If the location is absolute, convert it
to an RFC 3987 compliant URI and return it. If location is relative or
is scheme-relative (i.e., ``//example.com/``), urljoin() it to a base
URL constructed from the request variables.

children.name: process_request
children.comment:
Check for denied User-Agents and rewrite the URL based on
settings.APPEND_SLASH and settings.PREPEND_WWW

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
When the status code of the response is 404, it may redirect to a path
with an appended slash if should_redirect_with_slash() returns True.

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
If request.session was modified, or if the configuration is to save the
session every time, save the changes and set a session cookie or delete
the session cookie if the session has been emptied.

children.name: authenticate
children.comment: If the given credentials are valid, return a User object.

children.name: login
children.comment:
Persist a user id and a backend in the request. This way a user doesn't
have to reauthenticate on every request. Note that data set during
the anonymous session is retained when the user logs in.

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
Update the storage backend (i.e., save the messages).

Raise ValueError if not all messages could be stored and DEBUG is True.

children.name: order_fields
children.comment:
Rearrange the fields according to field_order.

field_order is a list of field names specifying the order. Append fields
not included in the list in the default order for backward compatibility
with subclasses not overriding field_order. If field_order is None,
keep all fields in the order defined in the class. Ignore unknown
fields in field_order to allow disabling fields in form subclasses
without redefining ordering.

children.name: is_valid
children.comment: Return True if the form has no errors, or False otherwise.

children.name: get_field
children.comment: Return a field instance given the name of a forward or reverse field.

children.name: redirect
children.comment:
Return an HttpResponseRedirect to the appropriate URL for the arguments
passed.

The arguments could be:

    * A model: the model's `get_absolute_url()` function will be called.

    * A view name, possibly with arguments: `urls.reverse()` will be used
      to reverse-resolve the name.

    * A URL, which will be used as-is for the redirect location.

Issues a temporary redirect by default; pass permanent=True to issue a
permanent redirect.
